<li id="cite_note-ConcerningGod1-12">^ <a href="#cite_ref-ConcerningGod1_12-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-ConcerningGod1_12-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMortimer_Adler">Mortimer Adler. <a href="http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman1.htm" class="external text" title="http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman1.htm" rel="nofollow">"Concerning God, Modern Man, and Religion (Part One)"</a>. The Radical Academy Adler Archive<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman1.htm" class="external free" title="http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman1.htm" rel="nofollow">http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman1.htm</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Concerning+God%2C+Modern+Man%2C+and+Religion+%28Part+One%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Mortimer+Adler&amp;rft.au=Mortimer+Adler&amp;rft.pub=The+Radical+Academy+Adler+Archive&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fradicalacademy.com%2Fadlergodmodernman1.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Mortimer_Adler"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-ConcerningGod2-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-ConcerningGod2_13-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFMortimer_Adler">Mortimer Adler. <a href="http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman2.htm" class="external text" title="http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman2.htm" rel="nofollow">"Concerning God, Modern Man, and Religion (Part Two)"</a>. The Radical Academy Adler Archive<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman2.htm" class="external free" title="http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman2.htm" rel="nofollow">http://radicalacademy.com/adlergodmodernman2.htm</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Concerning+God%2C+Modern+Man%2C+and+Religion+%28Part+Two%29&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Mortimer+Adler&amp;rft.au=Mortimer+Adler&amp;rft.pub=The+Radical+Academy+Adler+Archive&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fradicalacademy.com%2Fadlergodmodernman2.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Mortimer_Adler"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
<p><a name="Further_Reading" id="Further_Reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Mortimer_Adler&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: Further Reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further Reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Harry Ashmore, <i>Unseasonable Truths: The Life of Robert Maynard Hutchins</i> (New York: Little Brown, 1989).</li>
<li>Alex Beam, <i>A Great Idea at the Time: The Rise, Fall, and Curious Afterlife of the Great Books</i> (New York: Public Affairs, 2008).</li>
<li>Mary Ann Dzuback, <i>Robert M. Hutchins: Portrait of an Educator</i> (Chicago: University of Chicago, 1991).</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Amy_A._Kass" title="Amy A. Kass">Amy Apfel Kass</a>, "Radical Conservatives for a Liberal Education" (Ph.D. diss., 1973).</li>
<li>Tim Lacy, "Making a Democratic Culture: The Great Books Idea, Mortimer J. Adler, and Twentieth-Century America" (Ph.D. diss., Loyola University Chicago, 2006).</li>
<li>William McNeill, <i>Hutchins' University: A Memoir of the University of Chicago 1929-50</i> (Chicago: University of Chicago Press, 1991).</li>
<li>Hugh Moorhead, "The Great Books Movement" (Ph.D. diss., University of Chicago, 1964).</li>
<li>Joan Shelley Rubin, <i>The Making of Middlebrow Culture</i> (Chapel Hill: University of North Carolina Press, 1992).</li>
</ul>
